comments.author: @ParvezPrime
comments.text:
Lionel Messi is the first and only player to reach the milestone of 400 assists since the advent of modern football. Before that, only one footballer had managed to cross the 400 assist mark, and he was a player from the 40s and 50s, Hungarian legend Puskas, whose assist count was 404. That is, with just 5 more assists, Messi could become the highest assist giver in history. 

What is surprising is that along with these 400 assists, he also has 893 goals in his career. If you look at history, you will see that all the legendary players who have come after the advent of modern football have made their place in history either for goals, or for assists, or for visionary passing, or for magical play. But Messi is the only player who has done all these 4 things at the same time. 893 goals, 400 assists, visionary passing of 30-40 meters and magical football in every match, all of these are Messi's uniqueness. 

I always wonder how a player who has scored 893 goals can also provide 400 assists? How a player who has scored 400 assists can also provide 893 goals? 

When I think of the goalscorer Messi, I think that a player who is capable of scoring 893 goals should probably provide 200/250 assists at most, and those assists should be from simple horizontal passes or crosses. But no! Most of the assists of the goalscorer Messi who has scored 893 goals are defensive line breaking passes from behind the striker to the central position, i.e. assists from a playmaker. 

When I think of the playmaker Messi, I think that a player who is capable of scoring 400 assists should probably provide 250/300 goals at most. But how did this same player score 893 goals? That is the result of football IQ, position sense and perfect timing. 

 Messi is the wonder of football. You can't put him in any specific category. He is the master of football üîë 

G.O.A.T üêê
